Make hermetic-llvm's Linux system-header directories remote-execution-safe.

hermetic-llvm hands the Linux kernel + glibc system headers to compile actions
through TWO independent paths, and both inject a bare source-directory artifact
(one opaque directory node) rather than the individual header files:

  Path A -- cc_args(data = [..._directory]) in toolchain/args/linux: feeds the
  kernel/glibc headers to ordinary "complete" (target-config) compiles.

  Path B -- the kernel_headers / gnu_libc_headers cc_library targets
  (hdrs = ["include"]), consumed via @llvm-project's libcxx/libcxxabi/libunwind
  implementation_deps. This is the ONLY header source for the exec-config
  "stage0" runtime compiles, which receive no kernel-header cc_args at all.

Local sandboxed builds follow the directory symlink fine, but remote execution
must expand a source directory into each action's Merkle input tree; the
include/ subtree (e.g. include/linux/) is not enumerated and gets dropped,
giving "fatal error: 'linux/limits.h' file not found" on the exec-config
toolchain-bootstrap [for tool] compiles. It is deterministic once the action
cache is cold; warm action-cache hits skip the compile and mask the gap, so it
presents as flaky. A Bazel-side input-declaration issue, not a backend bug.

Three coupled changes:

1. directory.bzl gains an opt-in expand_files arg (set for the kernel + glibc
   header repos) that makes DefaultInfo carry the individual header files (a
   recursive glob, minus `make headers_install` byproducts) instead of one
   source-directory artifact, so the Merkle-tree builder enumerates every header.
   This fixes Path A. The macOS SDK sysroot also uses headers_directory but is
   left unexpanded -- expanding it would bloat every darwin *local* compile.

2. runtimes/module_map.bzl previously emitted one umbrella submodule per File in
   a source directory's DefaultInfo, assuming that is exactly one directory.
   With expand_files that DefaultInfo is a file list, which would emit one
   (invalid) "umbrella <file>" per header and fail -Wincomplete-umbrella. The
   generator now emits a single umbrella per source directory taken from
   DirectoryInfo.path; identical to the old behaviour for unexpanded
   directories, so darwin/macOS-SDK module maps are unchanged.

3. The kernel_headers / gnu_libc_headers cc_library targets change
   hdrs = ["include"] (one source-directory artifact) to
   hdrs = glob(["include/**"]), so every individual header becomes a declared
   action input for the exec-config stage0 runtime compiles. This fixes Path B --
   the path the expand_files change above does not reach.

Drop if/when hermetic-llvm ships an equivalent fix upstream
(https://github.com/hermeticbuild/hermetic-llvm).

